# SearchAutocompleteResult

**Class**

The result of an autocomplete query, including display lines and a coordinate.

## Declaration

```swift
class SearchAutocompleteResult
```

## Overview

You can use search and search autocomplete in sequence by passing a [doc://com.apple.mapkitjs/documentation/MapKitJS/SearchAutocompleteResult] object as the query parameter of a search. For example, you can present the display strings of a collection of search autocomplete results to the user while maintaining a mapping to the original [doc://com.apple.mapkitjs/documentation/MapKitJS/SearchAutocompleteResult] object. When the user selects a result, make a search request with the corresponding [doc://com.apple.mapkitjs/documentation/MapKitJS/SearchAutocompleteResult] object to retrieve more information about the place.

## Autocomplete results

- **coordinate**: The coordinate of the result when it corresponds to a single place.
- **displayLines**: Lines of text to display to the user in an autocomplete menu.

## Instance Properties

- **administrativeArea**: The name of the state or province of the place.
- **administrativeAreaCode**: The official abbreviation for the state or area.
- **alternateIds**: A list of alternate Place IDs that identify a feature.
- **areasOfInterest**: An array of common names of the area in which the place resides.
- **dependentLocalities**: An array of common names for the local area or neighborhood of the place.
- **fullThoroughfare**: A combination of the thoroughfare and subthoroughfare.
- **id**: The Place ID that identifies a feature.
- **locality**: The city of the place.
- **name**: The name of the place.
- **postCode**: The postal code of the place.
- **subLocality**: The name of the area within the locality.
- **subThoroughfare**: The street number at the place.
- **thoroughfare**: The street name at the place.

## Performing a search autocomplete

- **autocomplete(query, callback, options)**: Retrieves a list of autocomplete results for the specified search query.
- **SearchAutocompleteOptions**: Options you provide to constrain an autocomplete request.
- **SearchAutocompleteResponse**: An object containing the response from an autocomplete request.
